{"metadata":{"role":"sampleCode","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"roleHeading":"WWDC16","title":"Introducing Swift Playgrounds"},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"abstract":[{"text":"Learn more about Swift Playgrounds, the new iPad app that teaches coding using the powerful Swift programming language. Explore the featured content, complete with puzzles that help you master each coding concept. Learn more about the coding features of Swift Playgrounds and see how the editing experience was re-imagined for touch. Learn to use the included templates to build playgrounds and look at the available features in the new playground book format.","type":"text"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-408-Introducing-Swift-Playgrounds","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sampleCodeDownload":{"kind":"sampleDownload","action":{"overridingTitle":"Read Transcript","type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2016\/408\/","isActive":true}},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-408-introducing-swift-playgrounds"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"kind":"article","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Be the hero to change that by reading the transcript and providing notes! It’s super easy:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Related-Sessions","text":"Related Sessions","type":"heading"},{"style":"list","items":["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-413-Create-Your-Own-Swift-Playgrounds-Subscription","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-402-Whats-New-in-Swift","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-404-Getting-Started-with-Swift"],"type":"links"}]}],"references":{"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC18-413-Create-Your-Own-Swift-Playgrounds-Subscription":{"role":"sampleCode","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc18-413-create-your-own-swift-playgrounds-subscription","type":"topic","title":"Create Your Own Swift Playgrounds Subscription","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-413-Create-Your-Own-Swift-Playgrounds-Subscription","abstract":[{"text":"Swift Playgrounds is a revolutionary iPad app to teach coding with the powerful Swift programming language. Learn how to create your own content for Swift Playgrounds using the new template, and find out how to use the subscription format to host your own feed online for others to access.","type":"text"}],"kind":"article"},"WWDC16-Icon.png":{"type":"image","alt":null,"identifier":"WWDC16-Icon.png","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-Icon.png"}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16-402-Whats-New-in-Swift":{"title":"What’s New in Swift","type":"topic","role":"sampleCode","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-402-Whats-New-in-Swift","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-402-whats-new-in-swift","kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Hear about the newest features in Swift 3, the third major release of the safe, fast, and expressive language, and the first major release built with the open source community. Gain insight into the latest changes in Xcode including enhanced migration support to help move your code to Swift 3. Learn how you can get involved in the open source community at Swift.org.","type":"text"}]},"https://nonstrict.eu/wwdcindex/wwdc2016/408/":{"type":"download","identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2016\/408\/","checksum":null,"url":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2016\/408\/"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","title":"WWDC Notes","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16-404-Getting-Started-with-Swift":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-404-Getting-Started-with-Swift","title":"Getting Started with Swift","kind":"article","type":"topic","role":"sampleCode","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-404-getting-started-with-swift","abstract":[{"text":"Updated to include the latest features, syntax and best practices for Swift 3, this session introduces the basics of the Swift programming language. Learn the recommended manner in which to declare variables, define functions, work with fundamental value types, protocols, generics, and more. Explore some of the great features that make Swift a safe, fast, and expressive language.","type":"text"}]},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"type":"link","url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","title":"Learn More…","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn More…"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"},"WWDCNotes.png":{"type":"image","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDCNotes.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","alt":null},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16":{"title":"WWDC16","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDC16-Icon.png"},{"type":"card","identifier":"WWDC16.jpeg"}],"role":"collectionGroup","type":"topic","kind":"article","abstract":[